TuxDroidServer Unit Tests
=========================

Unit tests use Ceedling, CMock and Unity:

* Ceedling is a Ruby script easing the setup of unit tests
* Unity and CMock are C libraries providing unit-testing related functions


Prerequisites
=============

* Ruby
* gem install ceedling (not sure)


How To Run Unit-tests
=====================

cd test
rake test:all


Configuration
=============

All the configuration of unit-testing is done through the test/project.yml file.
For more details, see the documentation of Ceedling.


Documentation
=============

See files in test/vendor/ceedling/docs.

Online documentation:

Ceedling documentation: https://github.com/ThrowTheSwitch/Ceedling/blob/master/docs/CeedlingPacket.md
Ceedling intro:         http://throwtheswitch.org/white-papers/ceedling-intro.html
Unity documenation:     https://github.com/ThrowTheSwitch/Unity/blob/master/docs/Unity%20Summary.txt
Unity intro:            http://throwtheswitch.org/white-papers/unity-intro.html
CMock documentation:    https://github.com/ThrowTheSwitch/CMock/blob/master/docs/CMock_Summary.md
CMock intro:            http://throwtheswitch.org/white-papers/cmock-intro.html
